As affecting the political life capitolii is ex- tensively employed with regard to criminal proceedings. Since the punishment for some criminal offences was death, but for a much larger class was some penalty which entailed capitii machuti, the phrases res capitolii, causa soczims craincn capitale, radiatam capi- ’ tale, poem capitolii, taken by themselves, are ambiguous, and their force must in each case be determined by the context.
